byline.original: By Sheera Frenkel and Kevin Roose

docs.abstract: An emerging field, digital phenotyping, tries to assess people’s well-being based on their interactions with digital devices.
docs.snippet: An emerging field, digital phenotyping, tries to assess people’s well-being based on their interactions with digital devices.
docs.lead_paragraph: Your digital footprint — how often you post on social media, how quickly you scroll through your contacts, how frequently you check your phone late at night — could hold clues to your physical and mental health.

headline.main: How Companies Scour Our Digital Lives for Clues to Our Health
headline.print_headline: Scouring  Our Clicks  For Clues  To Our Health

docs.abstract: European Union officials announced the retaliatory moves it would take if the U.S. imposed levies on imported steel and aluminum.
docs.snippet: European Union officials announced the retaliatory moves it would take if the U.S. imposed levies on imported steel and aluminum.
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — European Union officials unveiled an array of tariffs on Wednesday that they would place on American-made goods if the United States followed through on President Trump’s plan to impose penalties on imported steel and aluminum, raising the specter of a trade war.

headline.main: E.U. Pledges to Fight Back on Trump Tariffs as Trade War Looms
headline.print_headline: Cranberries, T-Shirts and Bourbon: E.U. Vows Array of Tariffs to Fight Trump’s

docs.abstract: American Airlines is adding service between New York and Chicago. But shuttles were once more freewheeling affairs, serving food to everyone, even on short flights.
docs.snippet: American Airlines is adding service between New York and Chicago. But shuttles were once more freewheeling affairs, serving food to everyone, even on short flights.
docs.lead_paragraph: The announcement by American Airlines seemed to hark to another era: The airline would be adding shuttle service between New York and Chicago this spring — and serving free beer and wine, no less.

headline.main: A New Shuttle Service, Minus the 1980s Frills
headline.print_headline: Boarding Soon: A Shuttle With a Whiff of the 1980s Glory Days

docs.abstract: The new plant is part of an initiative by Toyota to invest $10 billion in the United States over the next five years.
docs.snippet: The new plant is part of an initiative by Toyota to invest $10 billion in the United States over the next five years.
docs.lead_paragraph: Five months after announcing that they would reward some American city with a $1.6 billion car plant and 4,000 jobs, Toyota Motor and Mazda Motor said on Wednesday that they had a winner: Huntsville, Ala.

headline.main: Toyota and Mazda Choose Alabama for $1.6 Billion Car Plant
headline.print_headline: Toyota and Mazda to Build $1.6 Billion Alabama Plant

docs.abstract: To comply with Europe’s General Data Protection Regulation, which goes into effect on May 25, internet companies have been updating their data policies. Here’s how you can benefit.
docs.snippet: To comply with Europe’s General Data Protection Regulation, which goes into effect on May 25, internet companies have been updating their data policies. Here’s how you can benefit.
docs.lead_paragraph: You have probably noticed a flood of emails and alerts from companies in the last few weeks informing you about changes to their privacy policies.

headline.main: Getting a Flood of G.D.P.R.-Related Privacy Policy Updates? Read Them
headline.print_headline: Don’t Ignore Notices Of Privacy Updates

docs.abstract: The Metrodome was replaced by U.S. Bank Stadium, which has drawn new offices, apartments, hotels, restaurants and a park to the area.
docs.snippet: The Metrodome was replaced by U.S. Bank Stadium, which has drawn new offices, apartments, hotels, restaurants and a park to the area.
docs.lead_paragraph: The first time Minneapolis hosted the Super Bowl, in 1992, a solitary sports bar and acres of parking lots surrounding the Hubert H. Humphrey Metrodome stood in testament to the stadium’s failure to generate private investment in the neighborhood, an area east of downtown.

headline.main: Super Bowl’s Minneapolis Stadium Brings a Surge in Development
headline.print_headline: A Stadium That’s Filling the Seats and the Surrounding Blocks

docs.abstract: The cars get all the attention, but it takes a lot of muscle to make one of the world’s biggest car shows happen.
docs.snippet: The cars get all the attention, but it takes a lot of muscle to make one of the world’s biggest car shows happen.
docs.lead_paragraph: The shiny new cars get all the attention. But behind the scenes at the Detroit auto show — officially called the North American International Auto Show — a small army prepares the city’s Cobo Center for the invasion of vehicles and their fans.

headline.main: A Look Behind the Scenes at the Detroit Auto Show

docs.abstract: Antitrust concerns and Murdoch family politics could keep Comcast from reprising its $60 billion bid, but Disney may yet have to step up its game.
docs.snippet: Antitrust concerns and Murdoch family politics could keep Comcast from reprising its $60 billion bid, but Disney may yet have to step up its game.
docs.lead_paragraph: Comcast may be the spoiler in a Disney-Fox show. The cable firm is considering whether to try to thwart the Mouse House’s $52.4 billion purchase of parts of Rupert Murdoch’s empire. The story has many moving parts, and the Walt Disney Company may yet have to raise its game.

headline.main: Comcast’s Interest in Fox May Force Disney to Raise Its Offer
